<h1 id="splunk-server-access">Splunk Server Access</h1>
<p>This document describes how to get access to the Splunk servers for operational support.</p>
<h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>

<ul>
<li>HMCTS email account</li>
<li>Connected to the VPN</li>
<li>Member of &lsquo;DTS Platform Operations&rsquo; or &lsquo;dcd_team_secops_v2&rsquo; Azure AD group</li>
<li>SSH Config for HMCTS Bastions</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="connecting-to-splunk-servers">Connecting to Splunk servers</h2>

<ol>
<li><p>Connect to the <a href="https://portal.platform.hmcts.net">HMCTS VPN</a>.</p></li>
<li><p>Request JIT access to HMCTS Bastion Server - https://myaccess.microsoft.com/
<code>text
SecOps Sandbox Bastion Server Access OR SecOps Production Bastion Server Access
</code></p></li>
<li><p>SSH onto bastion secops server
See here for a steps on how to do this: <a href="https://tools.hmcts.net/confluence/display/RD/Bastion">HMCTS Confluence bastion access</a></p></li>
<li><p>SSH onto required Splunk server via the SecOps bastion you&rsquo;re now logged into. You should be be able to login using your Azure Active Directory account details (assuming you&rsquo;ve been added to the JIT groups above).
<strong>Follow the instructions output from the SSH command</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id="additional-notes">Additional notes</h2>
<h3 id="access-package-configuration">Access package configuration</h3>
<p>The access packages &lsquo;SecOps Sandbox Bastion Server Access&rsquo; and &lsquo;SecOps Production Bastion Server Access&rsquo; can be found in the Azure Portal under &lsquo;Identity Governance&rsquo;, any updates and amendments to this should be made here.</p>
<h3 id="vm-authentication">VM authentication</h3>
<p>User access to splunk VMs are provided by Azure Active Directory (AAD) login, which is provisioned onto the VMs during deployment via the VM extension &lsquo;AADLoginForLinux&rsquo;; this saves us having to retrieve and exchange SSH keys. The VMs have not been joined to the HMCTS domain.</p>
